<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n06025j"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n06" href="#n06025j">N06 (VI.B.11)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n06all.htm#n06025j"> 25(j)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> 12 widowers</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">So they fell upon the plan of sending heralds through all the <font color="green">[twelve]</font> tribes of Israel, that all might come together unto the temple of the Lord. Then the heralds went out, the trumpet of the Lord sounded, and all the people ran together. And Joseph the carpenter, of the house and family of David, also cast down his axe, and went out to meet the heralds. <small> James DeQincy Donehoo, <a name="APOCD" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#APOCD"><cite title="source">Les The Apocryphal Life of Christ</cite></a> (1903) 26</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: A footnote cites the tradition that only <i><mark>widowers</mark></i> were summoned. </mm> </dd></dl>
